What are your favorite programming tools (editor, etc.)?
Editor: While working in Linux, I mainly use Sublime and Gedit.
On windows, I use notepad++
Compiler: gcc/terminal on linux, eclipse/IDLE on windows

Describe any work on other open-source projects.
I have worked on Bugheist and hackademic project from OWASP some time back. Bugheist is a tool for reporting bugs/issues and getting points for that. Hackademic deals with web application security.
Apart from that, I have recently worked with SPDX fixing some bugs. SPDX is a software license format.

List other GSoC projects you are applying to.
I would be applying to SPDX apart from inkscape.


Project Task: Developing a portal for unifying project,ideas,bugs and tasks to manage them
efficiently

Abstract: Providing an easy all-in-one website to upload and view different ideas,bugs,project
and tasks with the features of assigning, marking, grouping them under a category
for easy access and search.

Description:
1. A portal for registering new developers/contributors to upload bugs,report issues and
suggest ideas for development
2. The user can upload bugs,issues,ideas through the portal with the feature of marking
it as funded /non funded, grouping them by tags, assigning it to some other user.
3. Another user can view the project he/she may want to work on by searching with filters
4. A comment section where the contributors can let the user know that they are currently working on that project. A way for them to ask query regarding the issues.
5. Some of the main features of blueprint launchpad will be implemented.
6. A separate page where Janitorials tasks can be uploaded( Like fixing headers,
footers, documentation etc. which can be done by anybody. ) User can update their status of
fixing anything like that.
7. The home page will show all the recent bugs/issues/ideas submitted.



Work Plan

Post-application Period and Community Bonding Period:
Diving into inkscape documentations to improve my knowledge of working of     inkscape to build a better design specific to the needs of the organisation.
Working with the mentors as well as other community people to decide a UI design     for a quick start.[Phase-1]
Browsing through the types of bugs and issues currently on gitlab and launchpad
for a better view of what kinds of fields database may need.

Development Phase:

Phase-1 : Deciding a design modal to use for storing and accessing different kinds of data efficiently
Phase-2 : Implementing the above features.
Phase-3 : Writing Tests for code validity and testing them.
Phase-4 : A total review by the community to let me know of any issues or improvement and working on them,
Phase-5 : Integrating it with Inkscape and documenting the code for easy future use.

Tentative Work Period(Timeline):

Week 1( May 30 - June 6) [Development Phase-1]: Creating a basic model of what is needed, how it is needed and where it is needed
Basically working on the initial structure of the database, linking them together.
Week 2-3(June 7 - June 20) [Development Phase-2]: Start working on developing a user interface for registering and uploading of idea/project/tasks by a user. Giving a way for the user to edit them back.,assign them, mark them as funded or non funded, and if funded then by whom.
Week 4-5 (June 20 - July 2) [Development Phase-2]: Adding implementation for user to view other projects based on different filters and work on them by letting other users know.
Week 6-7(July 3 - July 16) [Development Phase-3] : Writing some basic tests to test the implementation
Week 8: (July 17 - July 23) [Development Phase-4]: Review by mentors as well as other community members to improve/fix the portal. They will given access to the portal for testing.
Week 9-10(July 23 - August 6) [Development Phase-4]: Fixing remaining bugs and improving UI to make the portal more flexible, usable and popular among people. Improvements according to the reviews.
Week 11:(August 7-August 13) [Development Phase-5] : Adding remaining documentation for future use
Week 12:(August 13-August 21) [Development Phase-5] : Integrating it with inkscape

Week 13-14(August 21 â€“ September 5): Working with the community to transfer bugs from launchpad and gitlab.

An easy to use all-in-one development project management system is ready.

Future implementation
We can auto-update the website showing the commits made by the user related to that task on gitlab.
